# The Docker build context is the repository ROOT, so this is the .dockerignore
# Docker actually reads (per-package ones are ignored). Crucially this prevents
# the host's node_modules (Windows pnpm symlinks, broken on Linux) from being
# copied into the image and clobbering the freshly-installed Linux modules.
**/node_modules
**/dist
**/.wwebjs_auth
**/.wwebjs_cache
**/coverage
**/*.log
.git
.env
*.env.local
.claude
